<item>
            <title>[AMQ-8569] mismatch in activemq-client osgi and pom dependency requirements</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-8569</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The activemq-client module has a &apos;provided&apos; dependency on xstream, meaning users do not get that dependency passed on, they need their own dependency on it. The osgi details in the activemq-client manifest however dont list it as optional, so it is required there. This dep and the mismatched requirement wasnt present until 5.16.2.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The details in the activemq-osgi manifest do list xstream as optional. It seems like activemq-client should also.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
